The paper discusses a distributed measurement infrastructure for the Internet, which falls under the category of network measurements and analysis. Therefore, cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the design trade-offs and algorithmic challenges, which could fall under the categories of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper analyzes the structure of the Internet, which could fall under the category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
